-- Shanghai index ends near 20-month high on policy support 
-- By Chen Yixin and Kazunori Takada
-- Thu Oct 09, 2014 03:10AM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, Oct 9 (Reuters) - China's key share index ended near a 20-month high on Thursday helped by policy support after Premier Li Keqiang said China would launch further investment in targetted industries.

The Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> unofficially finished up 0.3 percent at 2,389.28 points. The CSI300 <.CSI300> of the leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings gained 0.1 percent. Li said in published comments late on Wednesday that China would launch further "major" investment projects in information networks, water conservancy and environmental protection this year. [ID:nL3N0S33AM] Beijing Capital Co Ltd <600008.SS>, a water supplier and treatment firm, rose 3 percent and Hunan Yonker Environmental Protection Co <300187.SZ> climbed 3.7 percent.